  h2.
    What is binge eating disorder (BED)?

  p.
    Binge eating disorder, now a distinct diagnosis in DSM-5#[sup Â®], is characterized by#[sup 1]:

  ul.bullet
    li.
      Recurring episodes (at least once weekly for 3 months) of consuming a large amount of food in a short period of time, compared with others
    li.
       A feeling of a lack of control during an episode
    li.
      Marked distress regarding binge eating

  p.
    During a binge, adults with BED may eat much more rapidly than normal, eat until they are uncomfortably full, and/or eat alone out of embarrassment. They may feel disgusted with themselves, depressed, or very guilty afterward.

